                            <comment id="14438930" author="brettporter" created="Sun, 1 Jul 2007 22:36:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I found the default to work with the latest 2.3 - I wonder if this bug is reported against 2.2 (where it does indeed fail for me)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14438751" author="ahardy66" created="Mon, 2 Jul 2007 16:34:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Brett, did you run the test case?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Running the testcase with 2.3-SNAPSHOT  20070314204553 under linux with maven 2.0.6 and JDK 1.5, it doesn&apos;t work. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There are at least two other users on the list who confirmed that they are seeing this issue too. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Optimistically, I guess it means it&apos;s probably not a big issue. However assuming that you are using the testcase, it must be something with the environment. Are you using JDK 1.5?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14438917" author="brettporter" created="Mon, 2 Jul 2007 19:19:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;no, I ran it on a sample project. This is JDK 5 on Mac.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14438988" author="siveton" created="Sat, 7 Jul 2007 06:53:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added automatically  the javadocDir in the sourcepath&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17957477" author="olamy" created="Tue, 10 Jun 2025 03:24:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This project has moved from Jira to GitHub Issues. This issue was migrated to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-javadoc-plugin/issues/540&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;apache/maven-javadoc-plugin#540&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
